lead_paragraph: A moderate earthquake shook Central California on Saturday evening, but no damage or injuries were reported. The quake, measuring 4.4 on the Richter scale of ground motion, struck about 9:21 P.M., said Pat Jorgenson, a spokeswoman for the United States Geological Survey in Menlo Park, Calif. Ms. Jorgenson said the quake was centered about five miles northwest of Parkfield.
